title: Will a presidential candidate say Mog at BTC conference?

markets.question: Will a presidential candidate say Mog at BTC conference?
markets.description:
On July 25, rasmr (@rasmr_eth) tweeted that he was going to attempt to get a presidential candidate to say "mog" (see: https://x.com/rasmr_eth/status/1816506518558347559).

This market will resolve to "Yes" if any former or current Democratic or Republican party presidential candidates who participated in the 2024 election cycle, or Robert F. Kennedy Jr., says the word(s) "mog", "mogs", "mogged" and/or "mogging" at the 2024 Nashville Bitcoin Conference. Otherwise, this market will resolve to “No”.

Pluralization/possessive of the word will count toward the resolution of this market.

The resolution source for this will be video evidence of a candidate saying mog.

Note: It is not necessary for rasmr to be directly involved in the candidate saying mog in order to qualify for a "Yes" resolution.
